Package calc.model

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    CalcInterface
    This interface is implemented by RevPolishCalc and StandardCalc, instructing them to implement an evaluate method.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    CalcModel
    Evaluates expressions passed by the controller, so the controller can pass the answer back to the view.
    Entry
    The Entry class defines the values (read from an expression) that can be stored in a Stack.
    NumStack
    The NumStack class defines the stack of numeric values, read from a reverse polish expression.
    OpStack
    The OpStack class defines the stack of operator symbols, read from an infix expression.
    RevPolishCalc
    The RevPolishCalc class is used to evaluate postfix expression strings, by implementing the Visitor design pattern to traverse a binary tree of the expression, and calculate the answer.
    Stack
    The Stack class defines the list of entry values read from an expression.
    StandardCalc
    The StandardCalc class is used to evaluate infix expression strings, by implementing the Shunting Algorithm.
    StrStack
    The StrStack class defines the stack of strings, read from an infix expression.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    Symbol
    The enum Symbol defines the list of non-number tokens possible in an expression to be calculated.
    Type
    The enum Type defines the list of the types of values an Entry can represent.
  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    BadTypeException
    This class defines the custom exception BadTypeException, which is thrown when an incorrect getter type is called from the Entry class.
    EmptyStackException
    This class defines the custom exception EmptyStackException, which is thrown when the entries list of a Stack object is empty and either the top() or pop() method has been called.
    InvalidExpressionException
    This class defines the custom exception InvalidExpressionException, which is thrown when the user enters a string to be calculated, that contains invalid characters.
